'''Google Inc.''' ({{nasdaq|GOOG}} and {{lse|GGEA}}) is an [[United States|American]] [[public company|public corporation]], first [[Incorporation (business)|incorporated]] as a [[Privately held company|privately held corporation]] on [[7 September]] [[1998]], that designed and manages the [[Internet]]'s most used [[search engine]]. The company has approximately 8,000 employees and is based in [[Mountain View, California]]. [[Eric E. Schmidt|Eric Schmidt]], former [[chief executive officer]] of [[Novell]], was named Google's [[CEO]] when co-founder [[Lawrence E. Page|Larry Page]] stepped down.
